                  <tr>
                     <td><span class="ItemHeading">RedBrick Limited Releases the Earthdawn Gamemaster's Compendium!</span><span class="ItemType"> [<a href="http://www.earthdawn-classic.com/projects/selectProject.html;jsessionid=acszUBRjSan9?id=152144">Web Site Announcements</a>]</span><br><div class="ItemInfo">Posted on 
                           December 21, 2005 9:11 AM
                            by Anunnaki
                        </div>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td valign="top" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        Before science, before history, an era of magic existed in our world's dim past. Magic flowed freely, touching every aspect
                        of the lives of men and women of the Name-giver races. It was an age of heroes, an age of fantastical deeds and mythical stories.
                        It was the Age of Legend.<p/>In August 2005, <b>Earthdawn</b> was back with a new edition. Roll forward to December 2005.
                        For the first time since its initial release in 1993, this highly acclaimed fantasy roleplaying game is now available in an
                        all-encompassing format -- two comprehensive books containing everything required for years of play. The second of these two
                        books is the <b>Earthdawn Gamemaster's Compendium</b>, featuring:<p/>* Revised and streamlined game mechanics<br/>* Campaign
                        information on the province of Barsaive<br/>* Over a hundred creatures, dragons, spirits and Horrors, including a system for
                        creating and customizing your own creatures!<br/>* Guidelines on gamemastering and creating campaigns<br/>* Combines updated
                        content from over six previously-published supplements into one volume, along with new and optional rules.<p/><b>Earthdawn</b>
                        is set in a world of high adventure, high magic, and terrible danger. Trolls, dwarfs, elves, orks, and humans live side by
                        side with exotic races: the lizard-like t'skrang, the small, winged windlings, and the earthen obsidimen. In the Age of Legend,
                        bold heroes from all across Barsaive band together -- ready to fight for life and freedom against the remaining Horrors and
                        the oppressive Theran Empire, which seeks to bend the rebellious province again to their yoke. Through noble deeds and sacrifice,
                        the heroes of the world forge Barsaive's future, arming themselves for their daunting task with powerful magical spells and
                        treasures.<p/>This rulebook contains all the information gamemasters need to create and run ongoing adventures and campaigns
                        set in the popular <b>Earthdawn</b> universe.<br/><p/>Earthdawn Gamemaster's Compendium (RBL-101), ISBN 0-9582661-1-5, Hardcover
                        (524 pages), US$44.95. Visit http://www.earthdawn.com for more information.<p/>The <b>Earthdawn Gamemaster's Compendium</b>
                        is available in electronic format <b>NOW</b> for US$29.95 from <a href="http://www.drivethrurpg.com/catalog/product_info.php?products_id=3221">DriveThruRPG.com</a>.
                        The hardcover versions of both books is expected in January 2006. An announcement on print availability can be expected from
                        <a href="http://www.earthdawn.com">www.earthdawn.com</a> as soon as they are available. This release will be followed by <b>Ardanyan's
                        Revenge</b> -- an Earthdawn adventure -- in January 2006.<p/>Merry Christmas and Happy New Year to everyone from RedBrick!<p/>PS:
                        Don't forget <a href="http://www.drivethrurpg.com">DriveThruRPG.com </a> are having a 20% Holiday Sale! Details are on their
                        home page on how to take advantage of this offer. Applies to all of RedBrick's PDF products so use it while you can!<p/>
                        
                     </td>
                  </tr>
