                  <tr>
                     <td valign="top" class="TableCell">
                        To sweeten up the wait until the PDF release of the <b>Gamemaster's Compendium</b> (which will be available shortly on <a
                        href="http://www.dtrpg.com">dtrpg.com</a>), find a couple of updates in our <a href="http://www.earthdawn-classic.com/downloads/viewDownloads.html;jsessionid=amj_DKsQQ17e?id=2442">downloads
                        -> free stuff</a> folder, just in time for Christmas: <p/><b>KAER TARDIM (RBL-500) </b><br/>This sneak preview offers you
                        a taste of the fantastic <b>Earthdawn</b> adventures that await you and your friends. Everything you need to play is provided:
                        brief descriptions of the world of <b>Earthdawn</b> the rules of the game, descriptions of the characters who take part in
                        the adventure, and a short adventure called Kaer Tardim. In this story, a group of four adventurers volunteer to enter the
                        kaer of the village of Tardim to learn how Strathem, the village wizard, was killed, and to rid the kaer of whatever danger
                        lurks within it. <i>[PDF~14.67MB, erratas and typos fixed]</i><br/><i><b>NOTE:</b> This adventure uses a slimmed down version
                        of the Earthdawn rules, so some elements of game play in this adventure work differently in the full <b>Earthdawn</b> rules.
                        </i><p/><b>CHARACTER RECORD SHEETS (RBL-501) </b><br/>This file contains a full set of Character Record Sheets, and a two-page
                        Character Creation Summary. The Character Record Sheets can be adapted to hold beginning and experienced characters of any
                        kind and Circle, supporting the use of Adobe Acrobat Forms. <i>[PDF~5.36 MB, erratas and typos fixed]</i> <br/><b>Edit: </b>
                        Now there is also a plain version available, for easy printing. <i>[PDF~1.39 MB]</i> <b><font color="orange">NEW!</font></b><p/><b>DISCIPLINE
                        DESIGN (RBL-504)</b> <b><font color="orange">NEW!</font></b><br/>This file contains rules and guidelines allowing you and
                        your friends to design new Disciplines and talents for your <b>Earthdawn</b> campaign. Also included is a set of alternative
                        Discipline mechanics, taking the possibilities of character development to a whole new level. Requires the <b>Player's Compendium</b>
                        to use. <i>[PDF~7.53MB]</i>
                        
                     </td>
