                     <td><span class="ItemHeading">November Status Update</span><span class="ItemType"> [<a href="http://www.earthdawn-classic.com/projects/selectProject.html;jsessionid=acszUBRjSan9?id=152144">Web Site Announcements</a>]</span><br><div class="ItemInfo">Posted on 
                           November 26, 2005 10:43 AM
                            by Anunnaki
                        </div>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td valign="top" class="TableCellAlternate">
                        Hi everyone,<br/><br/>Well, it has been a while, but here is an update on where things lie. Firstly, the status of the Player's
                        Compendium hardcover. After some fun wrestling with InDesign CS2, Acrobat and Digital RIP compatabilities, we received the
                        galley proofs for the hardcover a couple of days ago. And they look great! However... Some other errors have crept into the
                        printing process and we're going to have to get these straightened out. So I'm afraid we're into another bout of to-ing and
                        fro-ing with the printer. Hopefully this is something minor which can be resolved quickly. You can have a look at some photos
                        at the Lore Merchant web site (http://lore-merchant.org). Josh has posted some pictures up, along with a couple of shots of
                        the problem. Realistically, with the time needed to do another galley run, I don't think we're going to be ready for orders
                        before Xmas. Hopefully I'm wrong.<br/><br/>In the meantime, we're just finishing up the Gamemaster's Compendium. Index is
                        underway, which, once complete, means we should have this up in PDF on DriveThruRPG in the next week or so. Coincidentally,
                        this means that the print version will probably be available at the same time as the Player's Compendium. It wasn't planned
                        this way, but looks like it's just how things have worked out. The Gamemaster's Compendium is 524 pages.<br/><br/>Richard
                        has already posted that Miniatures are available from the RedBrick web site. Thanks to those who have ordered early. If the
                        current lines go well, we will be looking at expanding it with new miniatures. Early days. Personally, I'm looking forward
                        to getting some time to do some painting. It's been too long... Please note the Merchandise Competition is on. Do leap in
                        and come up with suggestions. You've got nothing to lose! Also, the EDPT (http://www.edpt.org) is running a Writing Competition.
                        Details are on that site. We'll post a separate entry reminder here. Prizes are some Earthdawn books, so sharpen your pencils
                        and get writing!<br/><br/>Other news? Following on from the Gamemaster's Compendium is the adventure supplement Ardanyan's
                        Revenge, then the Name-giver's Compendium (with completely revised Disciplines, including the Shaman and Horror Stalker).
                        We've also got the other releases well under way for next year, including the Adventure Compendium and a brand new sourcebook
                        for Cathay. No firm release dates on these yet. Just letting you know that we're not sitting around here!<br/><br/>Lastly,
                        we are looking at softcover versions of the books as well (with a lower price point for those who might want a second book
                        or can't afford the hardcover). Plus there's a bunch of freebies sitting in the wings. And some other stuff which I'll tell
                        you about later.<br/><br/>OK, back to work! Be well,<br/><br/>JAMES FLOWERS<br/>Product Director, RedBrick Limited<br/>http://www.earthdawn.com
                        
                     </td>
                  </tr>
